Ahead of the presidential primary of the ruling All Progressives Congress, APC, aspirants from South East are currently in a closed-door meeting in Abuja. The meeting is taking place at Maitama, Abuja, home of former Imo State Governor, Senator Rochas Okorocha. Agenda of the meeting is still unknown, however, it may not be unconnected to moves by stakeholders to ensure that the party zones its ticket to the region. In attendance are Emeka Nwajiuba, Ogbonnaya Onu, Senator Ken Nnamani, Mrs. Uju Ken-Ohanenye and Okorocha. The Nation reports that Ebonyi Governor Dave Umahi was not in attendance following an emergency that took him back to his state. More to followâ€¦